The paper is about visualizing the internal geometry of neural networks and understanding their learning dynamics. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of visualization in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. Additionally, the paper touches on the topic of community structure in hidden units, which is a concept often studied in social network analysis (cs.SI).
